1. Panama issued a comprehensive draft of cryptocurrency regulation, recognizing digital assets as a legal means of payment;
2. Viewpoint: The recent decline in the crypto market may be related to the panic selling caused by Mt.Gox's transfer of BTC to repay debts;
3. Viewpoint: The next plunge in US stocks may pull BTC below $75,000, and returning to $100,000 requires a lasting change in macro liquidity;
4. Bitcoin spot ETFs had a total net outflow of $93.1572 million yesterday, and none of the twelve ETFs had a net inflow;
5. Ethereum spot ETFs had a total net inflow of $4.6817 million yesterday, and none of the nine ETFs had a net outflow;
6. New Jersey regulators ordered Robinhood and Kalshi to stop sports betting services;
7. The 27.9 million UNI unlocked by the Uniswap time-locked contract 8 days ago was transferred to Binance again by 2.5 million;
8. Ethereum whales transferred 16,800 to Binance in the past 16 hours ETH;
9. A whale purchased 20,654 AAVE with 1,906 ETH 5 hours ago.
